      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence that simulation setup was reviewed for operator error at MRL 2 Gradation 1 minimum.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by second analyst prior to production runs. Boundary condition specification, material property assignment, and turbulence model settings independently verified. No use errors identified during review. Gradation 1 requirement met for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model selection must be justified with reference to literature or sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published benchmarking studies for rotating blood pump flows (Hariharan et al., 2011; Bludszuweit, 1995). Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen et al.) applied with published constants. Sensitivity study comparing three turbulence models confirms k-omega SST provides lowest deviation from PIV data. Model form uncertainty acknowledged and bounded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, boundary conditions, material properties) must be traceable to measurement data or published specifications.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry derived from FDA-published CAD files (traceable). Inlet velocity profiles computed from measured flow rates. Blood viscosity set to 3.5 cP (Newtonian approximation, justified for high-shear pump environment). Fluid density 1056 kg/m3. All inputs documented in simulation log with source references. Dimensional tolerances for parametric study drawn from device design specifications."
    },
